recalls.Manufacturer: Jaguar Land Rover North America, LLC
recalls.Summary: Jaguar Land Rover North America, LLC (Jaguar Land Rover) is recalling certain 2014-2015 Jaguar F-TYPE vehicles previously remedied under Recall 14V-714.  The seatbelt harness connector which connects the Seatbelt Tension Sensor (STS) to the Occupant Classification Sensor Control Module (OCSCM) may not have been correctly wired.  As a result, the Restraint Control Module (RCM) may not accurately detect if an adult or child is occupying the seat.
recalls.Consequence: In the event of a crash necessitating air bag deployment, an incorrect classification may result in the passenger frontal air bag deploying even if there is a child in the front passenger seat, increasing their risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Jaguar will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the seat belt assembly and repair the seatbelt tension sensor harness as necessary, free of charge.  The recall began June 3, 2019.  Owners may contact Jaguar customer service at 1-800-452-4827.  Jaguar's number for this recall is H208.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Manufacturer: Jaguar Land Rover North America, LLC
recalls.Summary: Jaguar Land Rover North America LLC (Jaguar) is recalling certain model year 2014-2015 F-TYPE vehicles manufactured August 31, 2012, to October 22, 2014.  In the affected vehicles the seatbelt harness connector which connects the Seatbelt Tension Sensor (STS)  to the Occupant Classification Sensor Control Module (OCSCM) may not have been correctly wired. The OCSCM senses whether there is an occupant in the front passenger seating position, and the STS senses whether tension on the seatbelt indicates a child restraint is being used in the front passenger seating position.  Both sensors provide information to the restraint control module (RCM) which informs whether the front passenger airbag should be activated, depending on whether the sensors detect the seat is occupied and/or that it is occupied by an adult passenger.
recalls.Consequence: Should the STS not have been wired correctly, the front passenger air bag may not be suppressed, and may remain activated, even when a child restraint is placed in the front passenger seat or a small statured adult occupies that seat.  In the event of a crash necessitating deployment of the front passenger air bag, a child or small stature occupant may be at an increased risk of injury.
recalls.Remedy: Jaguar will notify owners, and dealers will correct the harness connector wire configuration, free of charge.  The recall began on December 3, 2014.  Owners may contact Jaguar customer service at 1-800-452-4827.  Jaguar's number for this recall is J047.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

issues.title: Supercharger Pulley Failure
issues.description: The supercharger pulley can separate or fail catastrophically, leading to sudden loss of power and potential engine damage. This is a known issue with the Eaton supercharger system used in the V6 S models.
symptoms: Loud grinding or metallic noise from engine bay
issues.fix_description: Complete supercharger replacement or rebuild with updated pulley design. Requires engine teardown to check for debris damage.
issues.prevention: Regular supercharger service, avoid aggressive driving when cold, monitor for unusual noises

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Driveshaft Failure
issues.description: The carbon fiber driveshaft can develop cracks or fail completely, causing vibration, noise, and potential loss of drive. More common in models with higher mileage or those subjected to hard driving.
issues.fix_description: Replace carbon fiber driveshaft with new or refurbished unit. Some owners opt for steel driveshaft conversion.
issues.prevention: Avoid hard launches, regular inspection during service, gentle driving until warmed up

issues.title: Timing Chain Tensioner Issues
issues.description: The timing chain tensioners can fail prematurely, causing timing chain rattle and potential engine damage if not addressed. This affects the 3.0L supercharged V6 engine.
issues.fix_description: Replace timing chain tensioners, guides, and chains. Engine must be partially disassembled.
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper specification oil, avoid extended idle periods when cold

issues.title: Electronic Power Steering Failure
issues.description: The electronic power steering system can fail suddenly, making the vehicle difficult or impossible to steer, especially at low speeds. NHTSA has received multiple complaints about this issue.
issues.fix_description: Replace power steering control module or entire steering rack assembly depending on failure mode.
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid parking with wheels fully turned for extended periods

issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Crashes
issues.description: The InControl Touch infotainment system frequently freezes, crashes, or becomes unresponsive. This affects climate control, navigation, and audio functions.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, module replacement, or complete infotainment unit replacement in severe cases.
issues.prevention: Keep software updated, avoid rapid inputs, regular system resets

issues.title: Water Pump Failure
issues.description: The water pump can fail prematurely, leading to engine overheating and potential catastrophic damage. This is particularly common in early production models.
issues.fix_description: Replace water pump, thermostat, and coolant. Check for engine damage if overheating occurred.
issues.prevention: Regular coolant system maintenance, monitor temperature gauge, address leaks promptly

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: The pop-out door handles can fail to extend or retract properly, potentially trapping occupants inside the vehicle. The electronic mechanism is prone to failure.
issues.fix_description: Replace door handle mechanism, motor, or complete door handle assembly.
issues.prevention: Keep handles clean, avoid forcing operation, regular lubrication during service

issues.title: Convertible Top Motor Failure
issues.description: The convertible top motor can fail, causing the roof to become stuck in partially open or closed position. This is common in models with higher usage.
issues.fix_description: Replace convertible top motor, hydraulic pump, or related components. May require top realignment.
issues.prevention: Regular operation to keep system lubricated, avoid operating in freezing conditions

issues.title: Fuel System Pressure Issues
issues.description: The high-pressure fuel system can develop leaks or pressure regulation problems, causing rough running, stalling, or reduced performance.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump, pressure regulator, or fuel rail components depending on specific failure.
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, replace fuel filter regularly, avoid running on very low fuel

issues.title: Suspension Control Module Failure
issues.description: The adaptive suspension control module can fail, causing the suspension to default to a fixed setting and loss of ride comfort adjustment.
symptoms: No response to drive mode changes
issues.fix_description: Replace suspension control module and update software. May require system recalibration.
issues.prevention: Regular software updates, avoid extreme driving conditions

issues.title: Transmission Overheating
issues.description: The 8-speed automatic transmission can overheat during aggressive driving or in hot climates, leading to reduced performance and potential transmission damage.
issues.fix_description: Service transmission fluid, replace transmission cooler, or rebuild transmission in severe cases.
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, avoid aggressive driving in hot weather, let vehicle cool between hard drives

editorial.tagline: British sports car soul with supercharged swagger
editorial.hero_blurb: The F-Type V6 S strikes the perfect balance between civilized grand touring and heart-pounding performance. With its supercharged soundtrack and lithe chassis, it's everything a proper British sports car should be.
editorial.essence: This is Jaguar's return to pure sports car form after decades away from the segment. The V6 S variant offers 90% of the V8's thrills with better balance and surprisingly tractable daily driving manners.
editorial.heritage: Spiritual successor to the legendary E-Type, the F-Type marked Jaguar's triumphant return to two-seat sports cars in 2013 after a 40-year absence from the segment.
editorial.design_philosophy: Ian Callum's team created a modern interpretation of classic Jaguar proportions - long bonnet, short overhangs, and sensual curves that capture light beautifully while maintaining aerodynamic efficiency.
editorial.motorsport_history: While the F-Type itself is primarily a road car, it draws from Jaguar's rich racing heritage including Le Mans victories and serves as the foundation for track-focused SVR variants.
editorial.engine_character: The supercharged 3.0L V6 delivers 380hp with immediate throttle response and a linear power delivery that builds excitement as revs climb, backed by the distinctive whine of forced induction.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed ZF automatic is telepathic in Sport mode, holding gears aggressively and delivering quick downshifts, though it can be sluggish in Comfort mode around town.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Aluminum architecture provides exceptional rigidity while the adaptive suspension strikes an impressive balance between compliance and control, with genuine adjustability between drive modes.
editorial.steering_feel: Electric power steering offers good feedback and appropriate weight, though it lacks the ultimate connection of hydraulic systems - still engaging enough for spirited driving.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive brakes with excellent pedal feel provide confident stopping power for both daily driving and occasional track use, though fade resistance could be better.
editorial.sound_signature: Distinctive supercharger whine accompanies a purposeful exhaust note that crackles and pops on overrun - unmistakably Jaguar and addictively theatrical.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving enthusiasts who want British character and daily usability, appreciate distinctive styling over outright performance numbers, and enjoy an engaging grand touring experience.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Track-focused drivers seeking ultimate performance, those prioritizing reliability over character, or buyers wanting maximum practicality and storage space.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for well-maintained examples with service history, as electrical gremlins can be costly. The 2016+ models received meaningful updates including improved infotainment and refined suspension tuning.

expertReviews.title: Why the Jaguar F-Type V6 S is the BEST sub-40k used ...
pros: Excellent value at under 40,000 used
380 horsepower supercharged V6 with fantastic exhaust sound
Outstanding handling and steering feel on country roads
Beautiful design inspired by E-Type with timeless appeal
Analog interior controls that feel tactile and engaging
Strong progressive brakes with good pedal feel
More practical boot space than rivals like Porsche 911/Cayman
Future classic potential with unique British charm
cons: Only a two-seater with limited practicality
Smaller paddle shifters compared to some rivals
expertReviews.verdict: The reviewer is completely sold on the F-Type V6 S as potentially the best value sports car on the used market. At under 40k, it offers 380hp performance, sublime handling, gorgeous looks, and fantastic exhaust sound. While less practical than some alternatives, it delivers exceptional driving experience and British charm that rivals like Porsche command premium prices for. Strong recommendation as an attainable future classic.

expertReviews.title: Should You Buy An Early Jaguar F-Type? || V6 S REVIEW (4K)
pros: Exceptional exhaust sound
High quality interior on par with German rivals
Excellent throttle response and instant supercharged power
Stunning design that captures attention
Good chassis that hides its weight well
Capable of both sporty driving and comfortable cruising
Creates sense of occasion and excitement
ZF automatic transmission is smooth and fast
cons: Reliability concerns with fuel injector issues costing 3000+ in first few months
Infotainment system will age without Apple CarPlay/Android Auto
Requires specialist repairs that even Jaguar dealers can't handle
expertReviews.verdict: An unbelievable achievement for Jaguar that captures imagination and passion. While not world-beating on paper, it succeeds in its mission as a spiritual E-Type successor. The V6 S makes the most sense in the lineup, offering supercar feelings without pretentiousness. Reliability issues are a real concern requiring financial cushion, but for those who can afford potential problems, it delivers an ownership experience that makes you feel special. Best suited for those wanting drama and emotion over pure track performance.

expertReviews.title: Jaguar's Last Great GT Car - F-Type S Review
pros: V6 engine has plenty of power
ZF gearbox with aggressive upshifts
Comfortable for cruising and long-distance GT driving
Good throttle response in race mode
Quiet cabin at highway speeds
Good value in used market
cons: Thick steering wheel makes car feel heavier
Steering lacks feedback and feels vague
Body roll and lack of agility when driven aggressively
expertReviews.verdict: A proper GT car that excels at comfortable long-distance touring but lacks the rawness and agility for aggressive driving. The F-Type V6 S offers good performance and value in the used market, representing one of Jaguar's last great GT cars with typical Grand Tourer qualities and compromises.

expertReviews.title: Should You Buy a JAGUAR F-TYPE? (Test Drive & Review ...)
pros: Very pretty car from most angles, especially front and side
Excellent exhaust sound and active exhaust system
Responsive throttle and steering, joy to drive
Good ride quality, not overly firm as expected
Driver-focused interior with quality leather and modern feel
Quick convertible roof (12 seconds, can operate up to 30mph)
Makes you feel special and cooler than you are
Good fuel economy for class (30mpg V6) and reasonable running costs
cons: Much smaller than expected, similar size to TT not DB9
Rear end looks pinched and odd, especially on convertible
Lack of standard features (no heated seats, no reverse camera, manual seat adjustment)
Build quality not on par with Porsche
Shallow boot space with no front storage
Some interior buttons showing wear despite being 2014 model
Jaguar badge positioned oddly flat on boot lid
expertReviews.verdict: Despite some disappointments in size and proportions, the F-Type V6 S is a special car that delivers joy and makes you feel cooler. The 380hp V6 is plenty quick with excellent sound, good ride quality, and driver-focused experience. While build quality trails Porsche and some standard features are missing, it feels more special and fun than clinical competitors. Recommended purchase despite imperfections - no car is perfect.

expertReviews.title: IS THIS THE BEST JAAAAG?! (2017 (67) Jaguar F-Type 3.0 ...
pros: Phenomenal V6 supercharged soundtrack
375 brake horsepower provides excellent performance without being terrifying
All-wheel drive system gives confidence in wet conditions
Beautiful British racing green and black leather color combination
Excellent build quality with no worn buttons or switches
Good fuel economy for a sports car (32 mpg on highway)
Substantial boot space for a sports coupe
Heated seats and steering wheel
Physical controls and dials
Well-maintained example with excellent service history
cons: Quite stiff suspension on country roads
Supercharger pump is a known expensive issue (2,900 repair)
Long car that can be difficult in tight spaces
expertReviews.verdict: The reviewer is extremely positive about this 2017 Jaguar F-Type V6 S, calling it 'fantastic' with no real flaws. The 375hp V6 supercharged engine provides excellent performance balance - fun without being scary like the V8. Key highlights include the incredible exhaust sound, all-wheel drive confidence, beautiful color combo, and surprisingly good practicality for daily use. Main concerns are the stiff ride and potential supercharger pump issues. At 31,995 with 54k miles, it represents good value in the sports car market.

expertReviews.title: Jaguar F-Type V6S Long Term Review & Ownership
pros: Incredible exhaust sound
Beautiful sports car design
Two distinct personalities (comfort and sport)
Excellent handling and low center of gravity
Fast convertible roof operation (12 seconds)
High-quality interior with premium materials
Reliable ownership experience
Gets positive attention from people
380 horsepower adequate for everyday driving
ZF automatic transmission is reliable
cons: High dash and door lines limit visibility
expertReviews.verdict: Owner considers this the best car he's ever owned after 1.5 years. The F-Type V6S excels as a weekend sports car with incredible exhaust sound, beautiful design, and dual personality. While it has comfort and visibility issues, the overall ownership experience has been highly positive with no reliability problems. Best suited for weekend driving rather than daily use.
